_extraction_workflow_latest.py` ‚Üí every hit shows `total_cats=1`\n     * `rg -n \"initialize_category_processing\\\\(\" /passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py`\n       ‚ÄĘ If any arg is `category_index=.*- 1` ‚Üí **bug still present** (note line #)\n       ‚ÄĘ If still used at category entry, confirm it **doesn‚Äôt** overwrite pointers pre-work\n     * `rg -n \"set_frozen_denominator\\\\(\" /passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py` ‚Üí verify freeze happens **before** resume gating\n     * `rg -n \"mark_category_complete\\\\(\" /passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py` ‚Üí if present, replace with `mark_category_completed(`\n     * `rg -n \"\\\\[PHASE_COUNTS\\\\]|supplier_cache_vs_linking_map divergence .*\\\\(lm_file:|cache_file:\" /*.log` ‚Üí confirm **file-grounded** wording\n     * `rg -n \"\\\\[CACHE_PICK\\\\]\" /*.log` ‚Üí verify fallback/primary selection logged\n\n  2. **Manually inspect** the supplier **progress callback** in `passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py`:\n\n     * It must call **only** `commit_supplier_progress(...)` per product (with frozen denominator), no deprecated writers.\n\n  3. Verify **resume gating order** for supplier extraction:\n\n     * Must be: **freeze ‚Üí fetch rp ‚Üí skip or slice with `start_offset` ‚Üí process**.\n     * Ensure `absolute_cat_index` vs `rp.cat_idx` are **both 0-based**; when equal, use `start_offset=rp.prod_idx`.\n\n  ### B) Log forensics (3 latest logs)\n\n  * Extract blocks where filtering shows work, then immediately prints a resume skip, e.g.:\n\n    ```\n    ūüďä NEEDS_FULL_EXTRACTION (6): [...]\n    ūüďč Resume skip: category 0 < 1 (no work)\n    ```\n\n    ‚Üí Collect 3‚Äď5 such sequences with timestamps.\n\n  * Confirm via earlier lines whether a **phase switch** or **eager init** just wrote `current_category_index=1` **before** any product commit.\n\n  * Confirm presence/absence of:\n\n    * `ūüĒí ...FROZEN DENOMINATOR...`\n    * `‚úÖ SINGLE_POINT_FREEZE / USING FROZEN DENOMINATOR`\n    * `‚úÖ RESUME HONORED: phase=supplier cat=‚Ä¶ prod=‚Ä¶`\n    * `PHASE TRANSITION: supplier ‚Üí supplier` (note timings and what was written just before)\n\n  ### C) Processing-state timeline reconstruction (5 snapshots)\n\n  * For each JSON, extract:\n\n    * `system_progression.current_phase`\n    * `system_progression.current_category_index`\n    * `system_progression.current_product_index_in_category`\n    * `system_progression.total_products_in_current_category`\n    * `resumption_ptr.cat_idx`, `resumption_ptr.prod_idx` (or wherever stored)\n    * `category_denominator_frozen`, `frozen_category_denominators` map\n\n  * Build a small table (time-ordered) to show how cat/prod pointers **changed (or failed to)** between `1strun.json ‚Üí start2ndrun.json ‚Üí endof2ndrun.json ‚Üí during 3rdrun.json ‚Üí final`.\n\n  * Point out where:\n\n    * cat index jumps **without** corresponding product commits\n    * denominators missing when resume banners are ‚Äúsuppressed‚ÄĚ\n    * cat index gets reset to 0 at run starts without justification\n\n  ---\n\n  ## ūüďč Deliverables (must produce all)\n\n  ### 1) Executive Summary (‚Č§ 10 bullets)\n\n  * Clear, testable statements of what‚Äôs working, what‚Äôs broken, and why we‚Äôre skipping extraction + zeroing indices.\n\n  ### 2) Evidence-backed Findings\n\n  For each finding:\n\n  * **Symptom** (quote log lines)\n  * **Cause** (quote code w/ file\\:line)\n  * **Impact** (what it breaks)\n  * **Proof** (processing-state deltas)\n\n  **Expected key findings to address explicitly:**\n\n  * Deprecated writer still used (or not)\n  * Eager category pointer writes\n  * Freeze order vs resume gating\n  * Method name mismatch for completion\n  * Amazon `total_cats=1` consistency\n  * Phase detection counts are file-grounded\n  * Cache fallback works (or not)\n\n  ### 3) Root-Cause Map\n\n  * A small cause‚Üíeffect graph (bullets ok) showing how (e.g.) *‚Äúeager pointer + no commits‚ÄĚ* ‚áí *resume skip even when work exists*.\n\n  ### 4) **Surgical Implementation Plan** (with diffs/snippets)\n\n  Produce **ready-to-apply** changes with context:\n\n  * **Supplier per-product writer**: replace any `update_processing_index(...)` with `commit_supplier_progress(...)` and show exact block.\n  * **Freeze order**: ensure `set_frozen_denominator(...)` happens **before** resume gating; provide snippet in place.\n  * **Resume gating**: demonstrate the logic (freeze ‚Üí rp ‚Üí slice) and show how `start_offset` is derived.\n  * **Remove off-by-one**: locate `initialize_category_processing(category_index - 1, ...)` and provide exact line diff to remove `- 1`.\n  * **Completion method**: change `mark_category_complete(...)` ‚Üí `mark_category_completed(category_url)`.\n  * **Amazon commits**: confirm/patch `total_cats=1` at every `commit_amazon_progress(...)`.\n  * **Phase detection**: if wording not file-grounded, patch the diagnostic lines to read counts from the actual files; include the exact logging change (we expect `(lm_file: N, cache_file: M)`).\n  * **(If needed)** Swap any early `init` calls for a **single ‚Äúentry commit‚ÄĚ** with `prod_idx=0`, after freeze and before extraction.\n\n  ### 5) Test Protocol (repeatable)\n\n  * **Scenario A: fresh run with categories that have work**\n\n    * Expect `FROZEN DENOMINATOR` then `commit_supplier_progress` per item, `‚úÖ RESUME HONORED` when resuming mid-cat.\n  * **Scenario B: category with zero work**\n\n    * Expect no product commits; do **not** regress the pointer; correct completion bookkeeping.\n  * **Scenario C: resume mid-category**\n\n    * Kill run mid-supplier; rerun; verify slice by `start_offset` and no double processing.\n  * **Scenario D: Amazon-only queue**\n\n    * Confirm `total_cats=1` everywhere; pointer increments via `commit_amazon_progress`.\n\n  ### 6) Acceptance Criteria (automatable via grep)\n\n  * `rg -n \"update_processing_index\\\\(\"` ‚Üí **0 hits**\n  * `rg -n \"initialize_category_processing\\\\(category_index=.*- 1\"` ‚Üí **0 hits**\n  * `rg -n \"commit_supplier_progress\\\\(\"` ‚Üí shows supplier loop and progress callback sites\n  * `rg -n \"commit_amazon_progress\\\\(.*total_cats=1\"` ‚Üí all Amazon callsites\n  * Logs show `ūüĒí FROZEN DENOMINATOR` **before** any resume gating for that category\n  * Logs show **no** `ūüďč Resume skip: category X < Y` immediately after a `NEEDS_FULL_EXTRACTION/AMAZON_ONLY` > 0\n  * State snapshots across runs show **monotonic** progress (no zeroing at run start unless truly at category 0 with no work)\n\n  ---\n\n  ## ūüďĆ Notes & Non-Negotiables\n\n  * **Do NOT** re-introduce any resume-pointer resets at category init; pointer advancement must remain owned by the **atomic commit** calls.\n  * **Keep** resume proof banners (we use them to audit).\n  * If you find additional blocking issues (e.g., early `continue` still present), include them in Findings with precise code locations and diffs.\n\n  ---\n\n  ## ūüß≠ Output Format\n\n  1. **Executive Summary**\n  2. **Detailed Findings (with file\\:line evidence)**\n  3. **Root-Cause Map**\n  4. **Patch Set (diffs/snippets & exact insertion points)**\n  5. **Test Protocol & Acceptance Criteria**\n  6. **Risk/rollback notes** (how to back out if a diff causes side-effects)\n\n  ---","images":[]},{"ts":1757953850593,"type":"say","say":"api_req_started","text":"{\"request\":\"<task>\\n**Mission**: With the **same attachments** I just provided (latest scripts, 3 newest logs, and 5 processing-state snapshots), perform a full audit to determine **what of the mainplan.md ( in root folder)\\n  integrated, what‚Äôs missing, what regressed**, and why the system **skips product extraction after the 2-step filter** and **zeros category indices across runs**. Produce a surgical\\n  implementation plan with diffs and a test protocol.\\n\\n  ## ūüď¶ Inputs (use these exact files)\\n\\n  **Scripts**\\n\\n  * `/passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py`\\n  * `/fixed_enhanced_state_manager.py`\\n\\n  **Latest logs (3)**\\n\\n  * `/run_